        <control>
                <id>MBSS-OS-RHEL8-010</id>
                <domain>System Security</domain>
                <description>Ensure permissions on bootloader config are configured</description>
		<command></command>
                <recommendation>To secure your system's GRUB configuration files and prevent unauthorized access to boot parameters, ensure appropriate permissions and ownership are applied based on your system's boot mode. &lt;br&gt;
For UEFI systems, modify `/etc/fstab` to include `fmask=0077`, `uid=0`, and `gid=0` options for the EFI partition, followed by a system reboot to enforce changes.&lt;br&gt;
For BIOS systems, update ownership to `root:root` and restrict permissions to prevent non-root access using `chmod u-x,go-rwx` for all relevant GRUB configuration files (`grub.cfg`, `grubenv`, `user.cfg`) in `/boot/grub2/`. &lt;br&gt;
This approach minimizes the risk of exploitation by non-root users who might otherwise view or alter critical boot settings.</recommendation>
                <expected_result></expected_result>
                <mandatory>Mandatory</mandatory>
        </control>
